=head1 DESCRIPTION

The number of objects that DataSync finds at your locations.

Applies only to Enhanced mode tasks
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/datasync/latest/userguide/choosing-task-mode.html).

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 AtDestinationForDelete => Int

The number of objects that DataSync finds at your destination location.
This counter is only applicable if you configure your task
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/datasync/latest/userguide/configure-metadata.html#task-option-file-object-handling)
to delete data in the destination that isn't in the source.


=head2 AtSource => Int

The number of objects that DataSync finds at your source location.

=over

=item *

With a manifest
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/datasync/latest/userguide/transferring-with-manifest.html),
DataSync lists only what's in your manifest (and not everything at your
source location).

=item *

With an include filter
(https://docs.aws.amazon.com/datasync/latest/userguide/filtering.html),
DataSync lists only what matches the filter at your source location.

=item *

With an exclude filter, DataSync lists everything at your source
location before applying the filter.

=back




